The Telegraph - Calcutta : Business

 Polaris profit jumps

 OUR BUREAU

 Oct. 17: Polaris Software Lab has reported a more than two-fold increase in its net profit for the quarter ended September 30 at Rs 18.49 crore compared with Rs 8.09 crore for the same quarter last year. Total income increased from Rs 176.74 crore for the quarter ended September 30, 2005 to Rs 235.42 crore for the same quarter this year.

 The group has recorded an almost 104 per cent jump in profit after tax at Rs 27.10 crore in the quarter ended September 30, 2006 compared with Rs 13.25 crore in the same quarter a year back. Consolidated total income increased from Rs 215.61 crore in the quarter ended September 30, 2005 to Rs 253.95 crore in the same quarter this year, a rise of 17.78 per cent.

 Arun Jain, CEO and chairman of Polaris, said, We will continue to focus on our core competency of banking and have launched the worlds first super-specialty centre for technology solutions for global investment banks. We have increased our investment in sales and marketing by Rs 4.5 crore and will continue to invest more in branding and marketing initiatives in a calibrated manner. 

 Bilt Q1 net up 

 On the back of robust demand, paper manufacturer Ballarpur Industries Ltd (Bilt) has reported a 31.8 per cent rise in net profit for the first quarter ended September 30, while it said it is mulling a price hike to be effective next month. 

 The company has posted a net profit of Rs 58.26 crore compared with Rs 44.20 crore in the corresponding quarter last year.

 Overall, the economy is doing well and there has been an increased demand from all segments, including educational, media and advertising, Bilt managing director R. R. Vederah said. Total income (net of excise) increased 21 per cent to Rs 529.91 crore for the first quarter in 2006-07 from Rs 437.92 crore during the July-September period in 2005-06.

 Indo Rama PAT dips 

 Polyester maker Indo Rama Synthetics India has reported a 74 per cent dip in profit after tax to Rs 8.73 crore in the quarter ended September 30 from Rs 33.67 crore in the corresponding quarter last year. Total income (net of excise) decreased to Rs 399.31 crore, down 16 per cent from Rs 478.21 crore during the year-ago period. 




